	(text "* Basic snubber\n  filtering, for\n  batteries with\n  long leads."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 82.55 81.28 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 0.762 0.762)
				(color 72 72 72 1)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "0cc1c253-ec27-4255-ae9d-1528c422ef95")
	)
	(text "* This selects the battery's THRM (PPTC) destination. By default, the Fuel Gauge is\n  selected, but when VUSB or VEXT is present, the battery charger will force itself as the\n  destination. ~{BC_PG} is pulled-up to 3.3V.\n* BQ25620's datasheet instructs the user to reference THRM to REGN, which is only active\n  when VUSB is present and valid. Out of this case, temperature information would not be\n  available, unless read by the MAX17055, which has a totally different wiring scheme\n  from the BQ. Also, MAX17055 is more power-efficient for this type of measurement\n  (BQ needs the ADC to be active, which increases Iq).\n* To force THRM to go to BQ, close THRM_BYPASS, and de-populate (remove) Rthrm."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 83.82 95.25 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 0.762 0.762)
				(color 72 72 72 1)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "6928f4e9-b225-4433-8426-061e4a2580fb")
	)
	(text "[input-vbat] Battery Input: Connectors, Protections and Fuel Gauge"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 132.08 41.91 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.778 1.778)
				(thickness 0.4064)
				(bold yes)
				(color 72 72 72 1)
			)
		)
		(uuid "a699ecb5-9527-4c9d-a8e4-7ab405e3f3fa")
	)
	(text "* For reverse-polarity\n  protection. DW01 does\n  not explicitly provide\n  it, nor does BQ25620.\n* Cap for less I_inrush,\n  but needs proper values."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 95.25 82.55 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 0.762 0.762)
				(color 72 72 72 1)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "c36ae506-f2cb-4ea7-8431-27a851314eb8")
	)
	(text "* Fuel gauge. The BQ25620 does not provide this functionality,\n  and it could be either costly (implementation-wise) or inefficient\n  (in terms of power consumption) to implement such a feature\n  in software, using whatever data the BQ25620 provides."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 162.56 49.53 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 0.762 0.762)
				(color 72 72 72 1)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "e5884bb3-b814-4e66-bc97-27145abaac3b")
	)
